EDIT:added last spell <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukilzadikandinsky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KilzadiKandinsky</A> at: 9/6/02 8:50:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uavgwiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AvgWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/02 6:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balance (No stupid ideas please)</span><hr size=1> I have been thinking about some &quot;balance&quot; ideas.  Once again these are only ideas but I did not see many of these discussed here.   When thinking about these, considerations taken into accout were:<br>
- Does it fit the RP persona of a wizard?<br>
- Is it too difficult to implement?<br>
- Will it tread too much on other classes toes?  Is it unique enough to stand by itself?<br>
-- Does the spell create possible exploits?<br>
-- Has these ideas been discussed elsewhere? Or am I just not able to find it?<br>
-- etc<br>
<br>
While I agree, more efficient nukes are needed along with the big blasts, I think wizards need some new tricks along their other lines.   I don't want to move too far away and become a generalist (aka druid) but I think the gap between what we do well, and what others do has closed way too much.  Especially in the area of Direct Damage.  Also, consideration must be given as to what might make wizards more desirable in xp groups where we are inadequate at all levels (yes even at 60 as I am).<br>
<br>
Since many other posts have already discussed making our damage spells faster, more efficient, more damaging, I am going to focus on some other areas.<br>
-----<br>
Defense .....<br>
<br>
When I watched LotR and played various D&amp;D games long ago, I noticed that spells like globe of invulnerability were part of the arsenal.  On the surface, it may seem that these be like divine aura/harm shield/etc, but I would like to add a twist to differentiate wizards.  Specifically, allow them to cast while within the globe.<br>
<br>
At lvl 20:  Minor Globe of Invulnerability<br>
Fast casting spell that has a duration of 10 seconds.  This would allow a wizard to root a mob, nuke when over aggro to get a kill, or gate.  Self only.<br>
<br>
At lvl 39: Globe of Invulnerability<br>
Fast casting again.  But last quite a bit longer -- say 15 - 17 seconds.   Self Only.<br>
<br>
At 49:  Group Globe of Invulnerability<br>
Always fast casting.  But now lasting like 15 - 17 seconds.  Enough time for an evac -- enough time for a lot of stuff.  Perhaps self only but now will help in groupability.  Lots of potential uses.  <br>
<br>
At 55: Greater Globe of Invulnerability<br>
This one lasts like 23 - 25 seconds.  Same as ealier self only -- but lasts a bit longer.<br>
<br>
At 60:  Bestow Globe of Invulnerability<br>
Mostly a raid idea.  Would help in mob positioning.  Save a cleric from death.  Save a wizard from overaggro  --- hehe.  My only concern with this is it is too similar to the cleric AA skill.   Maybe this should be an AA skill only.<br>
<br>
--------<br>
<br>
Along our teleport line ......<br>
<br>
Dimensional Box:<br>
The caster climbs into a dimensional box (not in same dimension) for a period of time.  You cannot move in this as the box is stationary.  However, you do reload the zone and end up right where you are.  So in effect, you abscond but dont go to the evac spot in zone.  This spell would have the purpose of removing all aggro without really leaving.  This spell has mostly raid useages for aggro control.  But I can see some other possible uses outside the raid scenario.  This is a fast casting spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
---------------<br>
Also along the teleport line ...........<br>
Dimensional phasing -- Self only (otherwise content avoidance would be more of an issue).   You are partially in the current plane of existance, and you are not.  This spell might have a 3 minute duration but helps serve the wizard to do exploration.   Also might allow the wizard to get to a group deep within a dungeon.  The wizard cannot cast while in between planes, but can move.  <br>
-------<br>
teleport line again.....<br>
AntiSummon:  This might be self only -- maybe not.  But being summoned is like being ported.   And being the &quot;masters&quot; of arcane transportation, we should be able to prevent this.  Duration of this, maybe a few minutes.   Whether or not this should be self only or not is debatable.<br>
<br>
----------<br>
Damage dealer role ...........<br>
Groupablity for sustained damage is an issue for wizards.  So, per the damage dealer role, I am thinking that a stackable spell that enhances ALL damage dealers currently in the group of the wizard is needed.  <br>
<br>
Damage Magnification: All damage done by the group containing the wizard would get a 5 percent or 10 percent increase (not sure what an appropriate percentage is).  Maybe the damage increase should scale with the number of people in the group too.   Once someone leaves the group with the wizard, they lose the *damage buff* effect.  All damage dealing spells and all weapon blows get this damage increase.   My hope with this is that it would help groupability of wizards while helping sustained damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
Once again, I hope these serve as some ideas or thought starters.  We are wizards -- we should be thinking out of the box. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1057<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/02 11:40 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balance (No stupid ideas please)</span><hr size=1> Mana regen, god upgrage the flappies!<br>
